HEADWORD: Cicatrizant
<hw>Cic"a*tri`zant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>cicatrisant</ets>, properly p. pr. of <ets>cicatriser</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A medicine or application that promotes the
healing of a sore or wound, or the formation of a cicatrix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cicatrization</ent>⟦br⟧
